        "name": "Trivial"
      },
      "assignee": {
        "display_name": "Pawel STAWINOGA",
        "name": "Pawel STAWINOGA",
        "email": "pawel.stawinoga@richemont.com",
        "avatar_url": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/512cc6b416147b1b631cbf283f248e10?d=https%3A%2F%2Favatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net%2Finitials%2FPS-5.png"
      },
      "reporter": {
        "display_name": "Pawel STAWINOGA",
        "name": "Pawel STAWINOGA",
        "email": "pawel.stawinoga@richemont.com",
        "avatar_url": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/512cc6b416147b1b631cbf283f248e10?d=https%3A%2F%2Favatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net%2Finitials%2FPS-5.png"
      },
      "created": "2025-08-08T16:34:02.629+0200",
      "updated": "2025-08-08T16:58:27.367+0200"
    },
    {
      "id": "130516",
      "key": "SFPSCA-3304",
      "summary": "Documenting recent processes",
      "description": "h1. Overview\n\nA few processes have not been documented yet and they keep appearing around and still require passing the same explanation. It would be great to consolidate the knowledge and write it down. This way everyone can benefit from it and it reduces repetitive quesitons and communication.\n\nh1. Actions\n\nCreate or update the following Confluence docs.\n\nh2. Submitting a new SFDC support case\n\nAccessing to [help.salesforce.com|http://help.salesforce.com] was a bit difficult when RM team prod a-accounts (system admins) had fake emails. It changed in Aug, 2025. RM team a-account have real emails now. It eases logging in to the help portal in CyberArk window.\n\n[https://richemont.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RCRM/pages/547389921/Creating+a+new+Salesforce+support+case|https://richemont.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RCRM/pages/547389921/Creating+a+new+Salesforce+support+case|smart-link]\n\nh2. Expiring creds around RM team\n\nThere are a few credentials, relevant mostly for the RM team which expire. One of them are GitLab project tokens which give access to GitLab repo. E.g. some pipelines use them to access the repo and run some actions (create a MR automatically).\n\n[https://richemont.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RCRM/database/549529880|https://richemont.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RCRM/database/549529880|smart-link] Confluence database tries to keep them all in one place. Maybe we will start using Confluence calendar instead in the future.\n\nh2. Onboarding a RM member\n\nWe’ve got a rare chance to collect the actions needed to onboard a new RM member. Some of the actions apply to any RIC new user (GitLab, Zscaler access, some AD/AAD groups). It will definitely helps in the future onboardings.\n\n[https://richemont.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RCRM/pages/495321486/Onboarding+a+RM+member|https://richemont.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RCRM/pages/495321486/Onboarding+a+RM+member|smart-link] \n\nh2. Setting up Plauti DuplicateCheck\n\nDuplicate Check is a managed package which premium license has to be linked to a new sandbox. We do it manually. Bhim pointed out a few discrepancies in the current guide so it was updated.\n\n[https://richemont.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RCRM/pages/463970259/Setting+up+Plauti+Duplicate+Check+in+a+new+sandbox|https://richemont.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RCRM/pages/463970259/Setting+up+Plauti+Duplicate+Check+in+a+new+sandbox|smart-link] \n\nh2. Zscaler connection client\n\nZscaler VPN is the main way to access RIC internal resources (e.g. GitLab). Setting it up requires a few steps and was described in [https://richemont.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RCRM/pages/551715621/Setting+up+Zscaler+VPN|https://richemont.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RCRM/pages/551715621/Setting+up+Zscaler+VPN|smart-link].\n\nh2. Granting access to GitLab Client360 repos\n\n[https://richemont.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RCRM/pages/463959738/Getting+access+to+Client360+Gitlab+repositories|https://richemont.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RCRM/pages/463959738/Getting+access+to+Client360+Gitlab+repositories|smart-link] got updated.",
      "status": {
        "name": "Closed",
        "category": "Done",
        "color": "green"
      },
