        "avatar_url": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/512cc6b416147b1b631cbf283f248e10?d=https%3A%2F%2Favatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net%2Finitials%2FPS-5.png"
      },
      "created": "2025-08-08T10:42:36.856+0200",
      "updated": "2025-08-11T19:43:27.323+0200"
    },
    {
      "id": "129969",
      "key": "SFPSCA-3303",
      "summary": "Migrate all pipeline jobs to a k8s GitLab runner",
      "description": "h1. Overview\n\nGitLab pipelines run on runners (agents - virtual machines). RIC DevOps deprecated some default runners and asked for using another ones, called {{k8s}}. We migrated most of our pipelines to {{k8s}}, however we keep getting emails from the DevOps team that there are still some pipelines using deprecated runners.\n\nAll pipeline jobs have to have a {{tags: k8s...}}, e.g. [link|https://gitlab.richemont.com/scm_project/ric/client360/salesforce-master/-/blob/master/.gitlab-ci.yml#L28]. Other tags like {{docker-runner}} or no tag at all means that the pipeline uses a deprecated or decomissioned runner.\n\nh1. Actions\n\nGo over all the following jobs in the gitlab-ci.yml file and list all that don’t have the {{tags: k8s...}}.\n\n* on the quality, validation, master branches in the salesforce-master repo\n* on pipeline/* branches in the [Tools repo|https://gitlab.richemont.com/scm_project/ric/client360/tools/-/branches]. \n\n\n\nAn email from the DevOps team has been attached below.",
      "status": {
        "name": "Closed",
        "category": "Done",
        "color": "green"
      },
      "priority": {
        "name": "Medium"
      },
      "assignee": {
        "display_name": "Sergiu TARANU",
        "name": "Sergiu TARANU",
        "email": "sergiu.taranu@richemont.com",
        "avatar_url": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/32d0ac48641d11aabb9bf18215f5ef98?d=https%3A%2F%2Favatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net%2Finitials%2FST-0.png"
      },
      "reporter": {
