        "email": "pawel.stawinoga@richemont.com",
        "avatar_url": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/512cc6b416147b1b631cbf283f248e10?d=https%3A%2F%2Favatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net%2Finitials%2FPS-5.png"
      },
      "created": "2025-08-06T12:49:34.241+0200",
      "updated": "2025-08-11T19:49:07.996+0200"
    },
    {
      "id": "126004",
      "key": "SFPSCA-3282",
      "summary": "Requesting user configured in the Manage Sandboxes Pipeline to get the admin access after refresh",
      "description": "Currently we have a Managed Sandbox pipeline, used for Creating and refreshing sandboxes.\n\n\n*Acceptance Criteria*\n\n* Pipeline page includes a required field: *Requester Username*.\n* After sandbox *create/refresh* completes:\n** The requester is *provisioned in the new/refresh sandbox* (user created or mapped).\n** An *email notification* is sent to the requester containing: *sandbox name*, *instance URL*, *username*, and *next steps* (e.g., set/reset password to access the Sandbox).\n* Failures are *logged* and surfaced in the pipeline output.",
      "status": {
        "name": "Open",
