      },
      "reporter": {
        "display_name": "Bhim WANKHEDE",
        "name": "Bhim WANKHEDE",
        "email": "bhim.wankhede@richemont.com",
        "avatar_url": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/ae75e408a0679d995b66ef9a2ccaa143?d=https%3A%2F%2Favatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net%2Finitials%2FBW-2.png"
      },
      "created": "2025-07-21T09:40:24.031+0200",
      "updated": "2025-08-12T08:37:35.026+0200"
    },
    {
      "id": "122403",
      "key": "SFPSCA-3245",
      "summary": "Warn about removing picklist dependency in a MR - continuation 2",
      "description": "h1. Overview\n\nThis is a continuation of the story [https://richemont.atlassian.net/browse/SFPSCA-3005|https://richemont.atlassian.net/browse/SFPSCA-3005|smart-link] & [https://richemont.atlassian.net/browse/SFPSCA-3203|https://richemont.atlassian.net/browse/SFPSCA-3203|smart-link]  to implement an automatic metadata guard that protects from a known deployment corner case issue.\n\nThe solution has been already merged to non-prod pipelines, but not prod one.\n\nh1. Implementation\n\n# Create a Confluence doc describing the solution.\n# Merge the new pipeline to the *prod* deploy automation.",
